Chandigarh, the common capital of the two states, recorded 42°C.
{{/usCountry}}
{{#usCountry}}
Chandigarh, the common capital of the two states, recorded 42°C.
{{/usCountry}}
{{^usCountry}}
Weather experts attributed the sharp rise in temperatures to persistent dry and hot northwesterly winds prevailing over northwest India. Large parts of northwest India – including Punjab and Haryana – are expected to remain under the influence of these hot winds this week, keeping maximum temperatures in the range of 43°C to 47°C in several cities.
{{/usCountry}}
{{#usCountry}}
